97
00:10:50,549 --> 00:10:52,813
[ Moaning ]

98
00:10:52,885 --> 00:10:56,753
Whatta ya saywe...
drag out that raft ?.

99
00:10:56,822 --> 00:10:58,983
Float on into Dawson ?.

100
00:10:59,058 --> 00:11:01,492
- [ Whines ]
- We need supplies.

101
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:04,688
- [ Whines ]
- You up for it ?.

102
00:11:04,764 --> 00:11:07,790
- [ Whines ]
- Okay.

103
00:11:07,867 --> 00:11:09,801
We leave in the morning.

104
00:11:17,143 --> 00:11:19,077
[ Whines ]

105
00:11:22,682 --> 00:11:25,014
%% [Drum ]

106
00:11:31,724 --> 00:11:35,160
%% [ Haida Language ]

107
00:11:36,362 --> 00:11:41,026
%% [ Others Join ]

108
00:11:53,446 --> 00:11:57,815
[Whispering]
Thykingdom come, thy will be done,

109
00:11:57,883 --> 00:12:00,852
on earth as it is in heaven.

110
00:12:00,920 --> 00:12:03,855
Give us this day our daily bread,
and forgive us our--

111
00:12:09,328 --> 00:12:12,092
I mourn the passing
ofyour father, Moses.

112
00:12:12,164 --> 00:12:15,133
I'll pray foryou
in your time to lead.

113
00:12:15,201 --> 00:12:19,069
Thankyou for sharing your food.
I'll return the favor.

114
00:12:19,138 --> 00:12:21,504
We expect nothing
in return, god-man.

115
00:12:21,574 --> 00:12:25,271
Get away from there.
Come on. Go, go, go.

116
00:12:26,912 --> 00:12:30,507
- No, no.
- To refuse is an insult.

117
00:12:37,156 --> 00:12:39,590
There is something ofyours
I want.

118
00:12:39,658 --> 00:12:43,890
Yoursoul, Moses.
Yoursoul.

119
00:12:43,963 --> 00:12:48,093
- Safe trip back.
- You wonder why God's punishingyou ?

120
00:12:48,167 --> 00:12:51,568
We've done nothing
to angeryour god.

121
00:12:51,637 --> 00:12:54,629
And yet your people
are starving.

122
00:12:54,707 --> 00:12:56,641
There must be a reason
for that.

123
00:12:56,709 --> 00:13:01,112
My grandfather spoke often of the time
when the caribou would disappear,

124
00:13:01,180 --> 00:13:06,675
a time when the thunder
in the earth would be followed
by the coming ofthe wolf.

125
00:13:06,752 --> 00:13:11,451
Ifwe are patient, we will be instructed
how to restore the balance.

126
00:13:11,524 --> 00:13:15,585
These are stories, Moses.
You cannot liveyour life by that.

127
00:13:17,897 --> 00:13:21,958
In your book,
there are stories.

128
00:13:22,034 --> 00:13:25,003
Ifyou care foryour people,

129
00:13:25,070 --> 00:13:27,903
you'll take them to live with
your relatives on the island.

130
00:13:30,776 --> 00:13:34,212
You wear the same collar
as the one beforeyou,

131
00:13:34,280 --> 00:13:36,214
butyourwords are hollow.

132
00:13:36,282 --> 00:13:39,183
Reverend Michael
underestimated the situation.

133
00:13:39,251 --> 00:13:42,311
Why let this suffering
continue ?.

134
00:13:42,388 --> 00:13:47,382
Moveyour people
before it's too late.

135
00:13:47,459 --> 00:13:49,484
It is good
you have a concern.

136
00:13:49,562 --> 00:13:53,726
